 Gerrards car hits 10-yr-old
Liverpool: Liverpool and England midfielder Steven Gerrard was involved in car accident in which a 10-year-old boy reportedly broke his leg. Gerrard was driving his Bentley in a Liverpool suburb when the accident happened near a school around 3:15pm. local time Monday, British news reports said on Tuesday. Gerrard stopped to comfort the youngster until an ambulance arrived. Gerrard later went to a police station where he produced his driving documents and made a statement. The injured boy was identified in British news reports as Jamie Halliwell. Steven Gerrard knelt down and held his hand and he seemed genuinely upset, the boys grandfather, Reg Rogan, told a British daily. You could tell he was in shock. (AP) 
